trend_summary: Across the series the highway-anchored suburb thickens: vacant lots and small fields give way to new cul-de-sac housing, a sizable mixed-use block by the western interchange, and extra warehouses along the rail corridor. Road widening and added parking shrink tree cover, yet parks and school grounds persist. Overall form remains mid-rise, car-oriented.
notable_changes: Large mixed-use/office complex constructed beside the western cloverleaf interchange.
Several green parcels in the east converted to low-rise residential subdivisions.
Expansion of warehouse and logistics buildings along the southern rail line.
Primary highway and service roads widened, with new ramps and bridges.
Noticeable reduction of scattered tree canopy and small fields as impervious surface grows.
